The Dunes Hotel was the tenth resort to open on the Las Vegas Strip, and operated from 1955 to 1993 on the grounds where the Bellagio hotel and casino currently stands. The Oasis Casino was a second, separate casino from the Dunes that was opened in 1983.
citation: pho003425. Neon in Nevada Photograph Collection. PH-00225. Special Collections and Archives, University Libraries, University of Nevada, Las Vegas. Las Vegas, Nevada. http://n2t.net/ark:/62930/d1z288.

title: Slide of Primadonna Club, Reno, Nevada, circa 1970s
body: The night view of the Primadonna Club, now Hilton's Virginia Street Casino, originally located on North Virginia Street in Reno, Nevada. Opened from 1964 to 1978, the Primadonna Club was marked by five, twenty-feet tall female sculptures which were located only feet away from the well known Reno Arch. Site Name: Primadonna Club (Reno, Nev.)
